{"id":14881759,"mediaExerciseId":"7e8e1f42-f8d1-4547-b25e-cd82260b69c3","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612470,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":735,"solutions":[{"id":5967062,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we will apply what we have learned about Spot and Forward Rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/9207fa0f6eb94b21a6fc197c108302f6/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":31,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/9207fa0f6eb94b21a6fc197c108302f6/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"An **Exchange Rate** is the value of a country's currency when expressed in another country's currency. A forward trade is an agreement to exchange currency in the future.\n\nThe forward exchange rate is the exchange rate that is agreed by the parties when the forward trade was made. It will be used in the future.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":176,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/4ac0f6096f196bd98a0814111586b324/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":89,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/4ac0f6096f196bd98a0814111586b324/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Therefore, a **90-day forward exchange rate** is the exchange rate that is agreed by the parties when the forward trade was made and will be used after 90 days or when the exchange happens 90 days after the forward trade was made.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":137,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/699578f2c948504879d140359ae84afb/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":69,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/699578f2c948504879d140359ae84afb/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"## a.\n\nWe are asked if the dollar selling at a premium or discount relative to franc.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"A currency is selling at **premium** if its forward exchange rate is *more than* its spot exchange rate. On the other hand, a currency is selling at a **discount** if its forward exchange rate is *less than* its spot exchange rate.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/444f7c30cd2bdfc32b67e917c6856989/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/444f7c30cd2bdfc32b67e917c6856989/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"The exercise states that the exchange rate for the Swiss franc is quoted as SF 1.50 in the spot market and SF 1.53 in the 90-day forward market. Since the forward exchange rate is **greater than** the spot exchange rate, the dollar is selling at a **premium** relative to franc.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":141,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/fbc124ecbe9c028ec83d50f5539357d9/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":72,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/fbc124ecbe9c028ec83d50f5539357d9/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"## b.\n\nWe are asked to explain if the financial market expect the franc to strengthen relative to the dollar.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7},{"columns":[{"text":"The dollar is selling at a **premium** relative to franc. This indicates that the value of the Swiss franc will decrease since more francs are required to purchase dollars.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/d86756bc47f65f2bd6140c9a45a9cca7/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/d86756bc47f65f2bd6140c9a45a9cca7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":8},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the financial market is not expecting the franc to strengthen. Rather, it expects that the value of the Swiss franc will **decrease** since more francs are required in purchasing dollars.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/df0610ef7a4ffcb1e763be53e91d3bd3/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":52,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/df0610ef7a4ffcb1e763be53e91d3bd3/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":9},{"columns":[{"text":"## c.\n\nIn this exercise, we are asked to identify the relative economic conditions in the United States and Switzerland.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":10},{"columns":[{"text":"Recall that the US Dollar is selling at a **premium**. Therefore, A higher inflation rate will occur since more francs are required in purchasing dollars. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":68,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/c61412c91e90cf45d0817dbd6bf57c86/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/c61412c91e90cf45d0817dbd6bf57c86/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":11},{"columns":[{"text":"As a result, this indicates a **poor economic condition** in Switzerland as there will be an *increase in inflation rate*  with regards to the exchange rate.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/45c3793d49d379b3eee89bc0f5f0fc4f/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/45c3793d49d379b3eee89bc0f5f0fc4f/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":12},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, we have applied what we have learned about Spot and Forward Rates.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/7d2604ff3a81ea15082c32588081cc7a/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/30/dde3c01b6f3eaabd30f657f59a5b574e/7d2604ff3a81ea15082c32588081cc7a/lateximg.png","width":497}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":13}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"1214d112-8167-439d-90e8-9af46fff1f56","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":13}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881760,"exerciseName":"2","page":735,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"fa4d8b42-30d1-45d6-aa1f-6c1ee163d0be","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-2-fa4d8b42-30d1-45d6-aa1f-6c1ee163d0be"},{"id":14881761,"exerciseName":"3","page":735,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1970e93f-d5d8-48ef-83f5-aa53a6a6889b","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-3-1970e93f-d5d8-48ef-83f5-aa53a6a6889b"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881758,"exerciseName":"7","page":732,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"0360b13b-7871-4529-9d26-2920161370f6","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-7-0360b13b-7871-4529-9d26-2920161370f6"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-critical-thinking-questions-1-7e8e1f42-f8d1-4547-b25e-cd82260b69c3"}